name: places/ChIJH09-DXUP2jERCg2KA3tyygw/reviews/ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnTUNZak56UlR3EAE
text:
{'text': "Lee Wee Nam Library at NTU is hands-down one of the best places on campus to get stuff done. Whether you're cramming for finals, working on a group project, or just need a quiet place to chill with your laptop, this library’s got you covered.

The space is bright, modern, and surprisingly cozy for a university library. There’s a mix of seating — quiet study zones, comfy lounge chairs, and group discussion rooms if you need to collaborate. The views from the windows are also a nice bonus, especially if you snag a seat by the glass.

Tech-wise, it's well-equipped with plenty of power sockets, printers, and fast Wi-Fi. The online resources and book selection are solid, especially if you're in engineering or tech — not surprising, given it's right next to the School of Computer Science and Engineering.

It can get pretty packed during exam season, so go early if you want a good spot. But overall, it’s one of the more comfortable and efficient places to study on campus.", 'languageCode': 'en'}

text: {'text': "The study area on Level 5 is generally quiet and comfortable, making it a nice spot to study. However, the air conditioning is not very strong, which can make it quite warm and uncomfortable at times, especially if you're seated near the windows.", 'languageCode': 'en'}

name: places/ChIJH09-DXUP2jERCg2KA3tyygw/reviews/ChdDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUNieFpXU25nRRAB
text: {'text': 'Went to the library as a visitor, not a student. But I was with a group of friends, and one of them is an NTU student. He asked if we could hang around the library as visitors. The girl who was in charge on Saturday 27/7/24 around 4 to 5pm was being very rude. She was extremely unfriendly. We were being as quiet as a mouse. But she was being very strict that we should only hang around the entrance area. This is understandable, however she could have been polite and friendly. What a fierce tigress! 4 stars only because the library environment was pretty nice and cozy. Zero star to that person in charge.', 'languageCode': 'en'}

text: {'text': 'A big library with multiple floors. There are water coolers and toilets at the side.\n\nIn the afternoon though, it can be very crowded, and the tables can be almost full. There may not be a single space on Level 5, but there could be some chairs on Level 4 (without access to power sockets).', 'languageCode': 'en'}
